## 🗺️ How the Map and Navigation Works

### Waypoints (Invisible Nodes)
The station graph has two types of nodes:
1. **Visible Nodes** — shown as dots on the map (platforms, exits, food stalls)
2. **Waypoints (Hidden)** — internal routing nodes prefixed with `WP_` or `Bridge_J`

**Why Waypoints?**
> Real station pathways aren't always direct. A path from Platform 1 to Platform 10 must go UP stairs → ACROSS the Foot Over Bridge (FOB) → DOWN the other side. Waypoints represent these intermediate structural points (stair landings, bridge midpoints) that passengers physically walk through but which don't need a label on the map.

### Rendering the Path (React-Konva, 3 Pass System)
1. **Pass 1** — Draw a glowing **cyan line** connecting all path node coordinates
2. **Pass 2** — Draw **cyan dots** on all intermediate path nodes (with labels)
3. **Pass 3** — Draw the **green START marker** and **red END marker** on top of everything

This layering ensures the start/end markers are never buried under the path line.

